P(T) = \frac{1-T^{m+1}}{1-T-T^2+T^{n+3}} =\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_i T^i 
\begin{align} 1-T^{m+1} &= (1-T-T^2+T^{n+3})\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_i T^i \\ &= \sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_i T^i -\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_i T^{i+1} -\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_i T^{i+2} +\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_i T^{i+n+3}\\ &= \sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_i T^i -\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_{i-1} T^i -\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_{i-2} T^i +\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} a_{i-n-3} T^i\\ &= \sum_{i=0}^{\infty} (a_i-a_{i-1}-a_{i-2}+a_{i-n-3}) T^i \end{align} 
